# Cursor AI Rules for Web Development Teaching



# Code Style
- Write clean, well-commented code
- Use descriptive variable names (e.g., 'userButton' instead of 'btn')
- Break complex operations into smaller, explained chunks
- Use modern best practices but explain legacy concerns


# Examples Should
- Be practical and relatable
- Start simple and gradually add complexity
- Include common UI patterns (forms, navigation, etc.)
- Demonstrate responsive design principles
- Show both desktop and mobile considerations

# Best Practices
- Emphasize semantic HTML
- Include performance considerations
- Cover cross-browser testing

# Do Not
- Use deprecated practices